# Launching a business is hard  
  
New tools are making it easier   
  
When I launched PhotoDrip it was just for LinkedIn headshots but as I used it I had a sense that there was something more that could be done. I started using it for content generation and it was a ton of fun.   
  
Fast forward a year later and social media is covered with AI generated content.   
  
There’s been a lot of buzz around Higgsfield lately. If you spend any time on Instagram or TikTok you have seen content produced by the platform by now whether you know it or not. Influencers are even selling their ‘workflows’ to other influencers.   
  
The funny thing about this output is there was no workflow. I dropped an image of me and an image of the product and pressed the button and thirty seconds later voila!  
  
Is this high quality? Can a skilled designer do better? Are there ‘tells’?   
  
For some people who are bootstrapping these are luxury questions. They are questions for people with time, money, and friends with skills willing to help them out.  
  
So while the artists and ethicists debate the merits of ‘AI slop’, there are people leveraging the technology, imperfect as it is, to bring their vision to life. To launch their new product or service. To get the word out.   
  
If you are one of those people let’s talk.   
  
  
  
  
